    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-12-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="890"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d890">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/487.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your December 4. Inform Clark Department approves his stand regarding location of
                    Receivers. His right in this matter seems fully <pb facs="0814" n="698"
                        xml:id="pg_698"/> covered under Agreement for Refolding Loan, article 4,
                    section A, paragraphs 3.</p>
                <p>He should bear in mind special agreement regarding location of German Receiver at
                    Monrovia without making any mention of same.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
